RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 26077. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEMPLE CITY RUN was forwardly placed along the inside in early stages, raced on the rail and got shuffled back at the seven sixteenths pole, lost ground and weakened to last, launched a four wide rebid at the head of the lane and kicked clear in deep stretch. NATIVE HELLRAISER raced in close contention in early stages, briefly edged up into striking distance then edged back and tracked the embattled duo around the turn, launched a rail bid at the head of the lane, took over a slim lead approaching the furlong marker, edged away then got outkicked in final stages. EYE OF THE PANTHOR came away last at the start and settled briefly while never far back, moved up four then three wide to challenge for the lead leaving the backstretch, vied outside of SARAHS BLUE BOY around the turn, continued in contention three paths wide into late stages and secured a share. SARAH'S BOY BLUE broke on top and held a slim lead then came under pressure near the half mile marker, vied with EYE OF THE PANTHER around the turn, shook free and briefly led the way then fought back when challenged by inside running NATIVE HELLRAISER, vied past the furlong marker then weakened late.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DISCREET INVASION was allowed to settle out of the gate and continued unhurried up the backstretch, saved ground and edged closer late on the turn, tipped three wide upper stretch and headed in pursuit, swept by the embattled duo near the sixteenth pole and finished going away. LUCKY LOUIE tracked the top pair up the backstretch, continued in range three wide around the turn, hustled up along the outside entering the lane, finished with response and just missed place. SCRUTINIZER dueled for the lead strides out of the gate and continued to battle with LANCELOT N ELAINE up the backstretch, began to edge away from rival midway around the turn then quickly took on the challenge from NOT ROCKET SCIENCE, dueled gamely inside of rival through the lane then got overtaken by the winner near the final sixteenth and flattened out. LANCELOT N ELAINE dueled with SCRUNTINIZER strides out of the gate and battled up the backstretch, matched strides to the mid-way point around the turn then came up empty and dropped back.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILTON STREET rated outside off the early pace, launched a three to four wide bid near the quarter pole, sustained an outside bid into the lane, steadily edged up closer and drove by late. ROBUST set the pace up the backstretch and held firm over close runner pursuers around the turn, led the way along the inside into late stages then got outkicked by the winner in deep stretch. LOUD BOY took a solid bump at the start and settled in the back, picked up the pace and gained on the inside late on the turn, came out and shifted three wide for the drive, roused forward into striking distance then yielded in the final sixteenth. Non-winners of $60,000 once or $45,000 twice allowed 2 lbs.; non-winners of $45,000 allowed 4 lbs.; maidens allowed 6 lbs. No nomination fee. No nomination fee. $400 to pass the ent ry box and $800 additional to start. $100,000 guaranteed which will first be reduced so as to allow $500 to be paid to each of the seventh through last place finishers with the remaining purse paid out as follows: 60% to the owner of the winner, 20% to se cond, 10% to third, 5% to fourth, 3% to fifth and 2% to sixth. SUPPLEMENTAL NOMINATIONS AT TIME OF ENTRY WITH A FEE OF $1,600 TO ENTER AND START. Starters named through the entry-box by the usual time of closing. Should this race not be divided and the en try number exceeds twelve (12), high weights will be preferred, then money earned. Different owners will have equal draw according to weights. The second parts of same owner entries will have no consideration over a single interest. Failure to draw into t
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENERAL SHIPMAN vied briefly in opening stages then took over the lead and set the pace up the backstretch, held firm along the rail over close running pursuers around the turn, cut the corner entering upper stretch, widened to a clear advantage while ridden out, felt rivals creeping up late, tapped a couple times and and held clear. DAWSON'S STORM broke in and bumped foes at the start then settled off the early pace, let out a notch and quickly moved up three to four wide near the quarter pole, sustained three wide bid through the lane, edged closer on the winner and captured place in final stride. GOOD LIKE MAGIC tracked the pace in the opening quarter then moved up into close contention entering the turn, hustled along two wide into the lane, ran on with response then got edged late for place. SINCERELY MINE took a solid bump at the start then drifted inward sharply and steadied losing ground, raced well off the early pace, picked up the tempo around the turn, came two to three wide into upper stretch and showed interest in the lane. U CAN DO U stumbled hard then was forced to steady when rival drifted in strides out of the gate, lost ground and raced in the back, continued reserved then hustled along five wide into the lane and passed tiring rivals. NAVE raced in early contention along the inside, hustled along the rail around the turn then gave way. OZONE got bumped at the start and chased near midpack in the opening quarter, failed to sustain bid into the turn, came four wide into the lane and had no late response. WHATDOYOUTHINKMARK was forwardly placed in the opening quarter, continued in contention and chased two wide around the turn then emptied out in the lane. THE STEWARDS POSTED AN INQUIRY LOOKING AT THE START, AFTER REVIEW NO ACTION WAS TAKEN

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARMING CHARLIE was forwardly placed around the first turn and stalked the leader up the backstretch, angled out a path and moved up midway around the turn to take over a slim lead, shook clear turning for home and kept to task under a steady encourgement.
